##Dictation | Tarek: My mother in Yemen is not crying now, I had a good winter vacation in Shanghai

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Now that my mom is facetiming me again, I'll tell her that the TV news she saw turned out to be fake. The son is safe in Shanghai is the best proof. Although she still watched the news on TV every day, she really stopped crying.

Dictation | Tarek

Organized by Jiang Haofeng

I'm Tariq, a sophomore at Shanghai Normal University, and I'm from Yemen. This winter vacation, I did not return to China, but chose to stay in Shanghai. My parents, my sister, my brother and my sister in Yemen were all worried about me when the NCP epidemic broke out. One of the things that worried me most was my mother.

In late January, my mother watched TV every day. We have some western TV channels in Yemen. My mother watched those reports on TV about the epidemic in China and was very scared. On the video link, she was crying all the time, telling me to hurry home. I know what she's worried about. I told my mother that all this stuff on TV is fake! I'm safe in Shanghai. There is indeed an outbreak in Wuhan, Hubei Province, China, and we have seen reports of it in Shanghai, and we see daily changes in the number of confirmed and suspected cases of new coronary pneumonia in Wuhan, throughout China, and around the world. I told my family that Wuhan had many cases and that I was safe in Shanghai. I just returned to Yemen during the summer vacation, this winter vacation will not return to the country.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tarek

Mom was really worried about my health at first. But through the video, she saw that I was healthy and emotionally stable, and gradually resolved this concern. Here at the Shanghai Normal University, in late January, we also began to do some measures to close the school gates. At first, I didn't feel comfortable. I didn't feel good. But gradually, I found that the school is really good for our students. For example, the housemaster aunt to take our temperature every day; the teacher online questions, but did not send us to do anything to go out of school to complete.

As an international student from an Arab country, I can eat the food of halal canteen in my school. The campus supermarket is open. The school even offered a scholarship in February ahead of schedule. I told the family everything. My parents were relieved to hear about it. Dad also wrote a thank you letter to Shanghai Normal University. When I translated the Arabic thank you note into English and sent it to the international student office, the teachers were surprised to receive a letter from their parents in Florida.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tarek told the teacher in the International Exchange Office of Shanghai Normal University that his father had sent a "cross-country parent letter" 

My father wrote: "My family has been very anxious since I learned of the spread of COVID-19 in China. I advise my son to return home as soon as possible. But to my surprise, he said he was safe and that there was no need to go back. The school didn't let him down, and all the remaining students got a lot of attention and begged me not to worry about his safety. I feel very comfortable with that and very grateful to the Great Nation of China."

In fact, I was able to study in China because of my father's great influence. When I was in high school, we were at war in Yemen. In my country, if a high school student got good grades, there was a good chance that he would try to go abroad to attend college. At that time, my classmates and I discussed, we all want to study in Holland. I told my dad what I thought. My father's advice was to go to China. My father is a history teacher. He has a very insightful point of view. In my mind at the time, he was a know-it-all. China, he told me, is now running fast. China is such a big country, an ancient country, running so fast, there must be many opportunities in the future. Dad told me: "Tarek, you have many dreams. For you, the best place to fulfill your dreams is China! "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Letter from Tarek's father to Shanghai Normal University

At that time in Yemen, I also have a lot of impressions of China. Like how the Chinese helped us build bridges. One of our largest local hospitals is also built by the Chinese. So I took my dad's advice.

And so, I did come to China. As soon as I came to Shanghai, I fell in love with the city. I started with a Chinese course at the Tongji University. That's when I met a Chinese friend. Later, I also went to this friend's house to play, their family members treat me as one of our people, I feel very happy. After eight months of studying Chinese, I went to the Shanghai Normal University, where I filled out my application form. My major is information and mechanical and electrical engineering.

This winter vacation, my Yemeni classmates in Shanghai, there are many people back home. It was all part of their plan. The reason why I did not return to China is that I worked as a translator for some Yemeni companies during the winter vacation last year. I would like to accept some experience this winter vacation. Now that the outbreak is here, I'm stuck in my dorm room. However, at least the school's arrangements are very thorough, I feel good. For example, after the implementation of the epidemic prevention and control measures, our school teachers set up several wechat groups for our foreign students —— A group that could speak Arabic, a group that could speak Russian... we chatted in the group, originally from different countries, do not know the students, now know, but also in the group chat very hi.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Oil Painting "Go Wuhan" by Song Wei, a teacher at Shanghai Normal University

In China, I also met a few Yemeni friends who live in Wuhan, some of whom are also international students. I've been facetiming with them, too. I found that their school also arranged them well. Including eating, learning and other aspects of the problem, the school is very well thought out. Although the outbreak there is a bit serious, but as long as people do not go out, it can be safe.

There are eight of us. My sister is one year older than me. I'm second in line at home. My youngest brother is five years old. My family, including my brothers and sisters, are relieved that China is fine now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"strike hard to fight against epidemic situation" by Qian you Yi, a student of product design grade 2017 at Shanghai Normal University

I think it's becoming more and more comfortable in China. Just over a year of study, life, but also let me feel the rapid development of China. I believe the outbreak is temporary.

I have a dream that in the future I can open a trading company and do import and export trade between China and Arab countries. I believe that my Chinese dream will come true..
